# .cursorrules for Writing and Note-Taking

## Core Configuration
{
  "projectContext": {
    "purpose": "Content creation and note-taking",
    "features": ["web-search-enabled", "markdown-support", "ai-assistance"]
  },
  "codingStandards": {
    "general": {
      "useMarkdown": true,
      "autoFormatting": true,
      "webSearchByDefault": true
    },
    "namingConventions": {
      "files": "kebab-case",
      "headings": "sentence-case"
    }
  },
  "editorPreferences": {
    "spellCheck": true,
    "grammarCheck": true,
    "wordWrap": true,
    "lineLength": 80
  },
  "aiAssistance": {
    "webSearch": {
      "enabled": true,
      "providers": ["Google", "Wikipedia"],
      "autoSuggest": true
    },
    "summarization": true,
    "citationGeneration": true,
    "languageOutput": {
      "default": "zh-TW",
      "excludeEnglish": true
    }
  },
  "markdownFeatures": {
    "syntaxHighlighting": true,
    "tableSupport": true,
    "footnotes": true,
    "taskLists": true
  },
  "templates": {
    "article": {
      "sections": ["Title", "Introduction", "Body", "Conclusion", "References"],
      "defaultTags": ["draft"]
    },
    "note": {
      "sections": ["Summary", "Details", "Questions", "Follow-up"],
      "defaultTags": ["quick-note"]
    }
  }
}

## Workflow Rules
1. **Content Creation**:
   - Use Markdown for formatting (headings, lists, links).
   - Enable `web-search` for research and fact-checking.
   - Leverage AI for summarization and idea expansion.

2. **Note-Taking**:
   - Organize notes with hierarchical headings.
   - Use `> ` for blockquotes and `- [ ]` for tasks.
   - Tag notes for easy retrieval (e.g., `#meeting`, `#idea`).

3. **Publishing**:
   - Export to HTML or PDF with preserved formatting.
   - Auto-generate a table of contents for long articles.

## Web Search Integration
- **Default Behavior**:  
  All queries trigger a web search unless explicitly disabled.
- **Citation Format**:  
  Automatically format references in Markdown (e.g., `[Source](URL)`).

## AI Features
- **Summarization**:  
  Highlight text and request a summary with `<!-- AI:summarize -->`.
- **Expansion**:  
  Use `<!-- AI:expand -->` to generate additional content.
- **Fact-Checking**:  
  Prefix queries with `<!-- AI:fact-check -->` for verification.

## Example Markdown Template
```markdown
# Title

<!-- AI:summarize -->
> Brief summary or abstract.

## Introduction
- Context or background.
- Key questions or goals.

## Body
1. Main point 1.
2. Main point 2.
   - Supporting detail.
   - [Source](https://example.com).

## Conclusion
- Summary of findings.
- Future directions.

<!-- AI:expand -->
```

## Notes
- Enable `spellCheck` and `grammarCheck` for polished writing.
- Use `<!-- AI:help -->` for a list of available AI commands.